Sentencas: A cobalt-free material, LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- (LNF), was applied as a potential cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) using chemically stable BaZr0.8Y0.2O3- (BZY20) electrolyte for the first time.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: LNF was synthesized, and this material showed a good compatibility with BZY20 at high temperatures.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anode supported BZY20 cell with the LNF cathode was fabricated and tested, which showed a decent cell performance of 217, 107, and 46 mW cm(-2) at 700, 650, and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This fuel cell performance was significantly higher than that for the cells using cobalt-free cathode and BaZrO3-based electrolyte in literature reports.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the polarization resistance of the LNF cathode was restricted to 0.15 cm(2) at 700 degrees C, which was quite small and even can be compared with that for some cobalt-containing cathodes for BaZrO3-based cells.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These experimental results indicate LNF could be an alternative and promising cathode for proton-conducting cells with BaZrO3-based ceramic electrolyte, providing an alternative route for choosing and designing their cathode materials.
Titulo: LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3- as a Promising Cathode for Stable Proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
